We had a breakfast there too, very expensive but incredibly rich both in quantity and diversity of food.	However, after checking-in and during breakfast, staff seemed unaware that we decided to include the breakfast option during our reservation and insisted that breakfast was not included in the price.	Reason why I dont give the hotel 5 stars is value, Its very expensive and its not that good!	Also, breakfast was hugely expensive--$90/2 but extraordinary.	Only negative was that like most nicer European hotels, they expect you to eat a large and very expensive breakfast buffet.	It is quite expensive but it's more than worth it.